.TH "batadv_neigh_ifinfo_new" 9 "batadv_neigh_ifinfo_new" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_neigh_ifinfo_new \- search and possibly create an neigh_ifinfo object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct batadv_neigh_ifinfo *" batadv_neigh_ifinfo_new
.BI "(struct batadv_neigh_node *neigh "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_hard_iface *if_outgoing "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "neigh" 12
the neigh node to be queried
.IP "if_outgoing" 12
the interface for which the ifinfo should be acquired
.SH "RETURN"
NULL in case of failure or the neigh_ifinfo object for the
if_outgoing interface otherwise. The object is created and added to the list
if it does not exist.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The object is returned with refcounter increased by 1.
